---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import aboutImage from '../assets/images/about.jpg';
---

<section id="about" class="py-24 reveal">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-14 md:gap-20 items-center">
      <div class="relative h-96 md:h-[560px] w-full md:col-span-2">
        <Picture
          src={aboutImage}
          formats={['avif', 'webp']}
          alt="Celeste in yoga pose"
          widths={[400, 600, 800]}
          sizes="(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 40vw"
          pictureAttributes={{ class: 'block h-full w-full' }}
          class="h-full w-full object-cover opacity-80"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-8 text-black font-semibold">About me</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Celeste spent the majority of her years as a dancer before finding Yoga. What began as a
            meditation practice to nurture her mind and overall wellbeing developed into a physical
            Yoga practice where Celeste found for the first time the opportunity to turn inward while
            moving outward. From outward performance to inward presence. This created the link
            between her love of movement and physicality with mental and spiritual wellbeing.
          </p>
          <p>
            Celeste is a trained Rocket<sup class="text-xs">™</sup>, Ashtanga and Vinyasa teacher.
            All classes offer an equal balance of energy and grounding stability, a chance to hit
            pause on the external world and tend to yourself. Dedicating herself to the practice and
            the teachings of Yoga Celeste creates a blend of dynamic practices that help students
            develop body and breath awareness, mental and emotional resilience, and most
            importantly, a chance to play!
          </p>
          <p class="text-black font-medium">Come and be part of our wonderful community!</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
